text: Highclare School is a private school in Birmingham, England. It teaches mostly girls and some boys aged 18 months to 18 years. It was started in 1932. It has three buildings in different areas of Sutton Coldfield and Erdington. They have a 100% pass rate at GCSE. ==References== Category:Schools in England Category:Buildings and structures in Birmingham Category:1932 establishments in the United Kingdom Category:1930s establishments in England
